-- Paulinho Says He’s Joining Spurs for $26 Million: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-07-02T08:09:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-02/paulinho-says-he-s-joining-spurs-for-26-million-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Spurs Signing  Brazil midfielder Paulinho said he’s joining Tottenham
Hotspur from Corinthians in a deal worth 17 million pounds ($26
million), the  Guardian reported .  “The other interest we got was from Inter Milan but the
only offer came from Tottenham,” the Guardian cited Paulinho,
24, as saying. “It was a big decision to go to a big club.
There comes a certain point when you need new challenges.”  Rooney Offer  Chelsea is preparing to offer Manchester United 20 million
pounds for Wayne Rooney, the  Daily Telegraph reported .  Although several clubs have been tracking the England
striker, Rooney is said to be most attracted by the prospect of
joining Blues manager Jose Mourinho at the west London team, the
newspaper added.  El Shaarawy Shortlisted  Chelsea is planning a move for AC Milan’s Stephan El
Shaarawy after Mourinho placed the Italian forward on a
shortlist of targets, the  Daily Express reported .  The 20-year-old El Shaarawy, who scored 16 goals in Serie A
last season, may be available for about 30 million pounds, the
newspaper added.  Bender Bid  Arsenal’s bid of 19 million pounds for Bayer Leverkusen
midfielder Lars Bender was rejected by the German club, the
 Daily Telegraph reported .  The Gunners are considering whether to return with an offer
of more than 20 million pounds for the 24-year-old or pursue
other holding midfielders, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
